@WillAyd have you seen this failure in the CI on other PRs?

```
=================================== FAILURES ===================================

self = <pandas.tests.indexes.datetimes.test_datetime.TestDatetimeIndex object at 0x13accba58>

    def test_stringified_slice_with_tz(self):
        # GH#2658
        import datetime
        start = datetime.datetime.now()
>       idx = date_range(start=start, freq="1d", periods=10, tz='US/Eastern')

pandas/tests/indexes/datetimes/test_datetime.py:105:

pandas/core/indexes/datetimes.py:1551: in date_range
    closed=closed, **kwargs)
pandas/core/arrays/datetimes.py:454: in _generate_range
    tz, ambiguous=ambiguous, nonexistent=nonexistent)
_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _

pandas/_libs/tslibs/conversion.pyx:1100: NonExistentTimeError
```

Hmm no that's a new one
@TomAugspurger judging by the test I think it's unstable given the upcoming DST transition. I'll open a separate issue

If I'm reading the test results correctly, the test failure is from line 105 here:

https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/0a61ecdf6b4ea61a67afb4e3862df79adc07053a/pandas/tests/indexes/datetimes/test_datetime.py#L101-L108

That particular line was changed 5 days ago in #25263.
